You have mistakenly specified more beneficiary benefit amounts than can be paid from Robert's IRA. Check each beneficary's allocation percentage or amount. Your plan results could change if all beneficiaries were paid.  This could be because your plan might be using the old logic of using 100% to sweep last remaining money after prior beneficiary benefits. A change has been made to how the program handles beneficiary benefits specified by percentages.   The old way applied the specified percentage to the remaining account balance, after any prior beneficiary benefit was handled. So a final 100% always got whatever remained.   The new way applies the specified percentage to the beginning balance as it was at the start of the sequence of beneficiary benefits. So a sequence of two beneficiary benefit instructions for 50% and then 100% will generate an error, since they are asking for more than 100% in total.  Use the new beneficiary parameter *Sweep Balance* to get any remaining balance.  Browse on the Web to *http://www.retirementforecaster.com/newrule.html* for more information.
